The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         BRIEFS
                  
	Midnapore, Aug. 10: Police have arrested five persons for lynching a man in Midnapore town today.     
	The deceased is yet to be identified. The man in a vest and a towel allegedly entered the house of Karuna Das around 8.30pm, the police said. When Das and his relatives told him to leave, he refused. An altercation followed after which residents of the locality tied him to a lamp post and beat him to death.        
	Krishnagar: A youth was killed and 17 persons were injured when a crowded bus hit a tree after losing control. The bus then fell into a ditch at Mukundapur on the Nabadwip- Burdwan road, about 100km from Calcutta, on Sunday. Police said Prasenjit Saha, 22, a resident of Chapra, died on the spot.         
	Tamluk: A physically-challenged man jumped to death from the Kolaghat bridge on the Rupnarayan on Sunday. Superintendent of police S.S. Panda said the body was fished out but he is yet to be identified.        
	Bolpur: A 60-year-old farmer was found dead with stab injuries on his throat in Margram, Birbhum district. Mrityunjoy Konar, a widower, used to stay alone. The motive of the murder has not been ascertained.                                                                                                                                                                   
